The course will draw attention to the essence, principles and definitions of international crimes, as well as to various possibilities to handle them on international or internal level. Special attention will be drawn to definitions and procedural aspects of international crimes in Estonia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the progressively developing discipline of international criminal law: to introduce students with respective international instruments, court practice and academic writings. To teach students to see and analyze the theoretical and practical issues of international criminal law.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course students have to: - be able to explain the principles and fundamental concepts of international criminal law; - be aware of topical issues of international criminal law and be able to discuss them; - be able to orientate in the relevant institutions and instruments
